column1: #Text=( flourished 1572 – 1600 ) , was an Elizabethan dramatist who worked primarily in the 1580s and 1590s .
#Text=He is also believed to have been an actor who specialized in clown roles .
#Text=He was connected with sixteen plays intended for Philip Henslowe ' s Rose Theatre , in partnership with other playwrights who also produced copy for Henslowe .
#Text=While mentioned as a dramatist by Francis Meres in 1598 , most existing information on his dramatic career is derived from Henslowe 's papers .

#Text=Since the name is common , it is not certain that the Robert Wilson who worked for Henslowe in 1598-1600 is the same man who was a prominent actor and occasional playwright in the 1580s ; yet many scholars consider it more likely than not that the records refer to one Robert Wilson and not two .
#Text=If this is correct , Wilson was acting with Leicester 's Men in the 1570s , and was praised along with Richard Tarlton for his " wit .

#Text= He is generally accepted as the author of The Three Ladies of London ( published 1584 ) , The Three Lords and Three Ladies of London ( published 1590 ) , and The Cobbler 's Prophecy ( published 1594 ) .

column1: #Text=This is consistent with the view that the two Robert Wilsons , the player with Leicester 's Men and Henslowe 's dramatist , were one and the same person ; it explains why Henslowe 's Wilson stopped writing in 1600 . [ 4 ]
